President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Mark Schneider as the Director of the Institute of Education Science in the Department of Education. Schneider is currently a vice president and Institute Fellow at the American Institutes for Research and President of College Measures. He has previously served as Commissioner of the National Center for Education Statistics and is known for his work in measuring the return on investment in higher education. Schneider earned his Ph.D. from the University of North Carolina in Chapel Hill in 1974.

Additionally, President Trump has announced his intent to appoint Nicole Nason as an Assistant Secretary of State for Administration. Nason is an attorney and senior government official who has previously served as Administrator of the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration and Assistant Secretary for Government Affairs at the U.S. Department of Transportation. She has also worked as an attorney for the Subcommittee on Crime in the U.S. House of Representatives. Nason founded and ran Project Koe in Connecticut, which focused on empowering women and improving health and fitness using traditional Japanese martial arts techniques. She holds a B.A. in Political Science and Government from American University and a J.D. from Case Western Reserve University.